title: Paintsville up to No. 6 in Mountain Top 10, Pulaski still No. 1
text:
/ Headlines List / Article 
HAZARD, Ky. (WYMT) -- The undefeated Paintsville Tigers (8-0) move up to No. 6 in the Alice Lloyd College Mountain Top 10 this week. 
Bell County drops to No. 9 after losing to Corbin; the Redhounds move up to the seven spot. 
The Top 5 remained the same after week eight of the high school football season. 
MOUNTAIN TOP 10 (After Week 8) 
1. Pulaski County (30)
